### Set API Key
@apiKey = your-secure-api-key-here
@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000

### Health Check
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### Send Simple Email
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/email/send
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "to": "recipient@example.com",
  "subject": "Hello!",
  "body": "This is a plain text email"
}

### Send Email with HTML
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/email/send
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "to": "user@example.com",
  "subject": "Welcome to MailerPro",
  "body": "Plain text fallback",
  "htmlBody": "<h1>Welcome!</h1><p>This is your welcome email.</p>"
}

### Send Email with CC and BCC
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/email/send
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "to": "primary@example.com",
  "cc": ["cc@example.com", "another-cc@example.com"],
  "bcc": ["bcc@example.com"],
  "subject": "Meeting Reminder",
  "body": "Don't forget about our meeting tomorrow at 2 PM",
  "htmlBody": "<h2>Meeting Reminder</h2><p>Don't forget about our meeting tomorrow at 2 PM</p>"
}

### Send Email with Reply-To
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/email/send
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "to": "user@example.com",
  "replyTo": "support@example.com",
  "subject": "Support Ticket #12345",
  "body": "Thank you for contacting us. Our team will respond shortly.",
  "htmlBody": "<p>Thank you for contacting us. Our team will respond shortly.</p>"
}

### Send Batch Emails
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/email/send-batch
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "emails": [
    {
      "to": "user1@example.com",
      "subject": "Welcome User 1",
      "body": "Hello User 1, welcome to our service!",
      "htmlBody": "<h1>Welcome!</h1><p>Hello User 1, welcome to our service!</p>"
    },
    {
      "to": "user2@example.com",
      "subject": "Welcome User 2",
      "body": "Hello User 2, welcome to our service!",
      "htmlBody": "<h1>Welcome!</h1><p>Hello User 2, welcome to our service!</p>"
    },
    {
      "to": "user3@example.com",
      "subject": "Welcome User 3",
      "body": "Hello User 3, welcome to our service!",
      "htmlBody": "<h1>Welcome!</h1><p>Hello User 3, welcome to our service!</p>"
    }
  ]
}

### Test Invalid Email
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/email/send
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "to": "invalid-email",
  "subject": "Test",
  "body": "This should fail validation"
}

### Test Missing API Key
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/email/send
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "to": "user@example.com",
  "subject": "Test",
  "body": "Missing API Key"
}

### Test Invalid API Key
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/email/send
X-API-Key: wrong-api-key
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "to": "user@example.com",
  "subject": "Test",
  "body": "Invalid API Key"
}
